Loom harness CLI

Usage: loom [OPTIONS] <COMMAND>

Workflow:
  plan    Interactive spec interview with optional initial anchors
  todo    Decompose the deterministic changed specs into the todo work epic
  loop    Execute task beads from explicit work roots or the active work epic
  gate    Quality gate — annotation-dispatched verifiers and LLM rubric
  inbox   Human decision queue for clarifies, blockers, and tune proposals

Inspection:
  status  Print cache health and work-epic status
  logs    Render (or tail) the most recent per-bead JSONL log
  spec    Inspect annotations and tooling dependencies for a spec

State:
  init    Initialize the workspace (create `.loom/` config + cache DB)
  use     Validate that a spec label exists in the cache
  note    Manage notes for a spec

  help    Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)

Options:
  -w, --workspace <PATH>  Workspace root. Defaults to the current working directory
  -A, --agent <BACKEND>   Override the agent backend for this invocation [possible values: claude, pi, direct]
  -h, --help              Print help
  -V, --version           Print version
